cker, environment, or system properties. For this library, it seems no extra dependencies or Docker are necessary. I should consider if the guidance could note avoiding the removed TypedActor. If I'm using JavaSerializer, I might need to enable config in ActorSystem. There's some ambiguity about whether avoiding obsolete APIs counts as “setup”. I'll need to inspect the release notes or documentation for clarity on what guidance to provide, aiming for a robust decision.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_5Dh0bA1sOFsLhqXi8BK8sOgJ|fc_0567786e827a5b40016a42046cdfd88197bdbdb4cf6bc0a67f", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request\nfor url in [\n 'https://pekko.apache.org/docs/pekko/2.0.0-M1/project/migration-guides.html',\n 'https://pekko.apache.org/docs/pekko/2.0.0-M1/typed/index.html',\n 'https://pekko.apache.org/docs/pekko/2.0.0-M1/actors.html',\n 'https://pekko.apache.org/docs/pekko/2.0.0-M1/serialization.html',\n]:\n    try:\n        with urllib.request.urlopen(url, timeout=10) as r:\n            text=r.read(200000).decode('utf-8','ignore')\n        print('URL', url, 'len', len(text))\n        for term in ['TypedActor','typed actor','dependency','pekko-actor-typed','allow-java-serialization','Java serialization','2.0']:\n            i=text.lower().find(term.lower())\n            if i!=-1:\n                print('TERM', term, text[max(0,i-200):i+300].replace('\\n',' ')[:700])\n    except Exception as e:\n        print('ERR', url, e)\nPY", "timeout": 60}}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_8W7ugZG6OzkXs9uVi7WH4rxx|fc_0567786e827a5b40016a42046ce0108197bfe0f36d2219f063", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "unzip -p ~/.m2/repository/org/apache/pekko/pekko-actor_2.13/2.0.0-M1/pekko-actor_2.13-2.0.0-M1.jar reference.conf | rg -n \"allow-java-serialization|java-serialization|serialization|typed|provider|artery|coordinated|loggers|slf4j|default-dispatcher|native|class\" -C 2 | head -240", "timeout": 30}}, {"type": "toolCall",