l\" class=\"page\">Release Notes (1.3.x)</a></li>     <li><a href=\"../release-notes/releases-1.2.html\"\nURL https://pekko.apache.org/docs/pekko/2.0.0-M1/actors.html len 199899\nTERM dependency s.html\">the new Actor API</a>.</p></div> <h2><a href=\"#module-info\" name=\"module-info\" class=\"anchor\"><span class=\"anchor-link\"></span></a>Module info</h2> <p>To use Classic Actors, add the following dependency in your project:</p><dl class=\"dependency\"><dt>sbt</dt><dd><pre class=\"prettyprint\"><code class=\"language-scala\">val PekkoVersion = \"2.0.0-M1\" libraryDependencies ++= Seq(   \"org.apache.pekko\" %% \"pekko-actor\" % PekkoVersion,   \"org.apache.pekko\" %% \"pekko-testkit\" % PekkoVersion % Test )\nTERM 2.0 cumentation\" class=\"header\">Security Related Documentation</a></li>   </ul></li>   <li><a href=\"release-notes/index.html\" class=\"page\">Release Notes</a>   <ul>     <li><a href=\"release-notes/releases-2.0.html\" class=\"page\">Release Notes (2.0.x)</a></li>     <li><a href=\"release-notes/releases-1.4.html\" class=\"page\">Release Notes (1.4.x)</a></li>     <li><a href=\"release-notes/releases-1.3.html\" class=\"page\">Release Notes (1.3.x)</a></li>     <li><a href=\"release-notes/releases-1.2.html\" class=\"p\nURL https://pekko.apache.org/docs/pekko/2.0.0-M1/serialization.html len 75384\nTERM typed actor torRef.html\" title=\"org.apache.pekko.actor.ActorRef\"><code>ActorRef</code></a></span> is described in <a href=\"serialization-classic.html#serializing-actorrefs\">Classic Serialization</a>. Classic and Typed actor references have the same serialization format so they can be interchanged.</p> <h3><a href=\"#deep-serialization-of-actors\" name=\"deep-serialization-of-actors\" class=\"anchor\"><span class=\"anchor-link\"></span></a>Deep serialization of Actors</h3> <p>The recommended approach to do deep seri\nTERM dependency \"> <label class=\"md-nav__title\" for=\"__toc\">Table of contents</label> <ul>   <li><a href=\"serialization.html#serialization\" class=\"header\">Serialization</a>   <ul>     <li><a href=\"serialization.html#dependency\" class=\"header\">Dependency</a></li>     <li><a href=\"serialization.html#introduction\" class=\"header\">Introduction</a></li>     <li><a href=\"serialization.html#usage\" class=\"header\">Usage</a></li>     <li><a href=\"serialization.html#customization\" class=\"header\">Customization</a></li>     \nTERM allow-java-serialization eason and for compatibility with older systems that rely on Java serialization it can be enabled with the following configuration:</p> <pre class=\"prettyprint\"><code class=\"language-ruby\">pekko.actor.allow-java-serialization = on </code></pre> <p>Pekko will still log warning when Java serialization is used and to silent that you may add:</p> <pre class=\"prettyprint\"><code class=\"language-ruby\">pekko.actor.warn-about-java-serializer-usage = off </code></pre> <h3><a href=\"#java-serialization-compa\nTERM Java serialization li><a href=\"serialization.html#serialization-of-pekkos-messages\" class=\"header\">Serialization of Pekko&rsquo;s messages</a></li>     <li><a href=\"serialization.html#java-serialization\" class=\"header\">Java serialization</a></li>     <li><a href=\"serialization.html#rolling-updates\" class=\"header\">Rolling updates</a></li>   </ul></li> </ul> </nav>    <ul class=\"md-nav__list md-nav__links\"> <li class=\"md-nav__item\"><a href=\"https://apache.org\"><i class=\"md-icon\">link</i> Apache Software Foundation</\nTERM 2.0 cumentation\" class=\"header\">Security Related Documentation</a></li>   </ul></li>   <li><a href=\"release-notes/index.html\" class=\"page\">Release Notes</a>   <ul>     <li><a href=\"release-notes/releases-2.0.html\" class=\"page\">Release Notes (2.0.x)</a></li>     <li><a href=\"release-notes/releases-1.4.html\" class=\"page\">Release Notes (1.4.x)</a></li>     <li><a href=\"release-notes/releases-1.3.html\" class=\"page\">Release Notes (1.3.x)</a></li>     <li><a href=\"release-notes/releases-1.2.html\" class=\"p\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1782711405646}, {"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_8W7ugZG6OzkXs9uVi7WH4rxx|fc_0567786e827a5b40016a42046ce0108197bfe0f36d2219f063", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "17-  # Loggers to register at boot time (org.apache.pekko.event.Logging$DefaultLogger logs\n18-  # to STDOUT)\n19:  loggers = [\"org.apache.pekko.event.Logging$DefaultLogger\"]\n20-\n21-  # Filter of log events that is used by the LoggingAdapter before\n--\n28-  logging-filter = \"org.apache.pekko.event.DefaultLoggingFilter\"\n29-\n30:  # Specifies the default loggers dispatcher\n31:  loggers-dispatcher = \"pekko.actor.default-dispatcher\"\n32-\n33-  # Loggers are created and registered synchronously during ActorSystem\n--\n36-  logger-startup-timeout = 5s\n37-\n38:  # Log level used by the configured loggers (see \"loggers\") as soon\n39-  # as they have been started; before that, see \"stdout-loglevel\"\n40-  # Options: OFF, ERROR, WARNING, INFO, DEBUG\n--\n71-  # Library extensions are regular extensions that are loaded at startup and are\n72-  # available for third party library authors to enable auto-loading of extensions when\n73:  # present on the classpath. This is done by appending entries:\n74-  # 'library-extensions += \"Extension\"' in the library `reference.conf`.\n75-  #\n76-  # Should not be set by end user applications in 'application.conf', use the extensions property for that\n77-  #\n78:  library-extensions = ${?pekko.library-extensions} [\"org.apache.pekko.serialization.SerializationExtension$\"]\n79-\n80-  # List FQCN of extensions which shall be loaded at actor system startup.\n--\n92-  # Pekko installs JVM shutdown hooks by default, e.g. in CoordinatedShutdown and Artery. This property will\n93-  # not disable user-provided hooks registered using `CoordinatedShutdown#addCancellableJvmShutdownHook`.\n94:  # This property is related to `pekko.coordinated-shutdown.run-by-jvm-shutdown-hook